BENIN – The move by authorities of the Edo State owed-Ambrose Alli University (AAU), Ekpoma, to reopen the university for academic activities, collapsed as a result of the resolve of the university’s academic and non-academic staff to sustain the ongoing nation-wide strike in the institution. The authorities of the university had on Thursday, May 26 this year, directed students to return to campus for academic activities. Our correspondent, who monitored the situation at the university on Thursday, reported that the institution was deserted, weedy and devoid of any form of academic and administrative activities. -Advertisement- All departments, faculties and offices, except a few offices in the university’s administrative building, were shut. The university’s workers vowed to continue the strike till its suspension by their national leaderships and the satisfactory resolution of the salary crisis in the university. Our Correspondent observed that there was no visible vehicular traffic and movement of students in and out of the university.